data: After Ruth Tinney adopts her 38-year-old plumber, Kevin Jacob Koellisch, then dies, Kevin feels he is entitled to her estate.
After high school student Joey Fischer breaks off his relationship with his girlfriend, the unbalanced mother of the girl exacts her revenge.
Rabbi Fred Neulander conspires to kill his wife Carol.

After 81-year-old Marjorie Nugent went missing for a whopping nine months, police finally begin to investigate. Her body is found in Bernie Tiede's freezer, who was also, conveniently, her business manager.
The affluent Dr. Dirk Greineder kills his wife May.
Successful restaurant owner Anjette Lyles is unable keep a husband because they just keep dying off and when her daughter comes close to death, eyebrows begin to raise.
Leo Gleese and his wife, Hazel Stanley Gleese, elderly newlyweds and new members of the Fountain of Life Church, are murdered and their "adopted son" Reverend John Canning, is arrested.
It seemed clear to everyone that pharmacist Chester Radecki was killed by Daniel J. Martinez, but would a jury think so too?
Richard DeCaro hires someone to kill his wife, Elizabeth.
The mistress of Gary Knepp gets carried away when she arranges for the murder of her lover's wife, Carol.

data: A supposed ballet dancer is the prime suspect in the 1995 murder investigation of Wanda Cowger Kuzmichev.
The 1991 high-profile Kay Sybers murder case is investigated.
Glenn Evans is murdered because he killed his girlfriend, while driving under the influence.
A land dispute leads to a shootout where Sgt. John Chambers is shot, and his police dog is murdered.
The murder case of Trent DiGiuro is detailed.
A Sunday school teacher, youth soccer coach and investment broker is accused of the 1991 murders of lawyer Ernest Brendel, his wife and their 8-year-old daughter.
After losing a bitter campaign Judge Daniel McDonald offs his rival's partner, James Klein.
The bizarre John Pinder is accused of the gruesome Rex Tanner and June Flood murders.

data: The Larry Streeter murder case is unusual because the suspect is 19-year-old paraplegic, and wheelchair bound, racing champion, Ted Ernst.

Yvonne Mathison's husband, a sergeant in the local police department, says he accidentally ran her over with his van. The evidence says otherwise.
Authorities determine that the murder of cosmetic king, Constantine Dean Milo, was arranged by the victim's own brother.

Baker Steven Lucas, the son of a former mayor, city councilman and Realtor, bludgeons his mother, Bette Calvert Lucas, to death.
83-year-old Rolf Neslund is shot, cut up and burned after an argument over his retirement fund.
Sandra Maloney is strangled and set on fire but coincidentally, or not, her husband John is a 19-year veteran of the Green Bay Police Department's arson division.

table-1549-565.caption: Season 5
data: The death of local madam, Sylvia Landry, is convenient for the community's affluent citizens because after all, she was threatening to reveal her client list in a tell all book.
When the extra-marital affair between Linda C. Brown and Kevin Cummings, both of the Santa Monica Police Department, goes sour, one of them uses a gun to make a point.
Local business rivals, T.K. Harty and John Henry Mooney, elevate their feud to murder for hire.

A cantankerous city commissioner, Enrique Zambrano, is the primary suspect in the 1988 beating of married couple Robert and Barbara Mishell and the star witness in the case, Luis Reyna, is found decapitated.
Dr. Rebecca Johnson pays for her naivete with her life after being conned by Alan Michael Johnson, who by the way, is no relation.

Tina Biggars, a Catholic graduate student, begins living the life of prostitution that she was originally only just studying. Unfortunately for her, she met Ken Trachinda who had other things on his mind.
The family and friends of Steven L. Harvey, a local jazz musician newcomer, fight to bring his killers to justice.
After authorities declare the death of Lawrence Ocrant a suicide, his children find a way to prove that the case was botched and was in fact, murder.
Bobbi Holman Williams, owner of a local upscale restaurant, is murdered and the conspiracy to kill her involves her husband.
Prominent pediatric neurologist, Dr. John Malmstrom, is murdered and his wife goes on trial.

table-1549-561.caption: Season 11

table-1549-917.caption: Cast
data: David grew up in a tough neighborhood, and lost many childhood friends to violent deaths and jail sentences, but was saved from the streets by his tennis coach and mentor. He was eventually recruited to the Virginia Military Institute, from which he knows Nathan, on a tennis scholarship. In response to problems in his beloved hometown, David and his mother helped form a neighborhood drug task force. David begins a relationship with Kira, a casting director for Bunim-Murray Productions. This is a violation of the rules, and Kira lost her job as a direct result. David knew Nathan from VMI before they joined the show. David naturally has one blue eye and one brown eye.
